model_explanation: S1 emphasizes that Sue is the only person who received apples, so S2 contradicts it by saying someone else also got apples.
S1 talks about what Sam gave Bill, while S2 talks about what Sam did not give to Mary. These statements are independent.
S1 means that Mary is the only person who got oranges, but S2 says Ellen also got oranges, which contradicts S1.
S1 specifies who received apples (only Ellen), and S2 states that Tom didn’t receive apples. These statements are independent since they refer to different people directly.
S1 is about which single item Rob received (only bananas), but S2 talks about Rob receiving a different fruit (oranges), which doesn't contradict or entail S1. They are about different items.
if Bill only got bananas, it follows that he didn’t get grapes. So S2 is entailed by S1.
if Ellen only received oranges, it is implied that she didn’t receive any other fruit, like grapes. S2 is entailed by S1.
S1 states that Mary is the only recipient of bananas, but it doesn’t directly say anything about Ellen. S2 simply adds information about Ellen, making them independent statements.
S1 talks exclusively about what Bill received (bananas) and doesn’t say anything about Tom. S2 is an independent statement about Tom not receiving bananas.
if Sue only got oranges, she did not get any other fruit, such as grapes. S2 is therefore entailed by S1.
